OL,6,F"He took the knife out of his pocket.
OL,7,FI ran away and he chased me with the
OL,8,Fknife and tackled me to the ground and
OL,9,Fstabbed me repeatedly.
OL,11,F"That's what happened."
OL,13,FMr Haynes asked: "The struggle that
OL,14,Fensued resulted in him disarming you?"
OL,16,FThe teacher replied: "That not true.
OL,17,FHe brought the knife and attacked me
OL,18,Fwith it and chased me and dragged me
OL,19,Fto the ground and stabbed me
OL,20,Frepeatedly until he was dragged off."
